           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Car dealerships in North America revert to pens and paper after cyberattacks on software provider</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      NEW YORK (AP) — Car dealerships in North America are still wrestling with major disruptions that started last week with cyberattacks on a company whose software is used widely in the auto retail sales sector. CDK Global, a company that provides software for thousands of auto dealers in the U.S.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/06/24/car-dealerships-in-north-america-revert-to-pens-and-paper-after-cyberattacks-on-software-provider/"  >(WYATTE GRANTHAM-PHILIPS, Associated Press, KGET 17, NBC)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
